{"id": 225063408, "title": "House Speaker survives latest attempted ouster by Conservatives", "text": "\"I find it very disturbing the Conservatives are attacking everything they don't control,\" he said. The Bloc Qu\u00e9b\u00e9cois voted with the Tories, but the Liberals and NDP had enough votes to defeat the motion. Government House leader Steven MacKinnon said the Opposition vote was meant to delay government work and create distrust in democratic institutions. \"What they seek to do is create chaos and create disorder,\" MacKinnon said in the House earlier Tuesday. Fergus declined to comment. \"It won't be appropriate for me to comment on something that's before the House,\" he said. Following the video incident, Fergus apologized and said the video was intended for a longtime friend and wasn't supposed to be played in public. A House of Commons committee looked into it and recommended disciplinary action but not that Fergus be fired. He was fined $1,500. This report by The Canadian Press was first published May 28, 2024.", "summary": "The effort to oust Fergus failed by a vote of 142-168 after the NDP sided with the Liberals, with both accusing the Conservatives of undermining democracy and its independent institutions.", "url": "https://www.nationalobserver.com/2024/05/29/news/house-speaker-survives-conservatives", "image": "https://www.nationalobserver.com/sites/nationalobserver.com/files/styles/nat_social/public/img/2024/05/29/b483b294e2d9ee26cafaf4d9f0919c001b139546fc11e423fb67969c68c7b5ca.jpg?itok=ORnLQo6X", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 13:05:31", "author": "Mickey Djuric", "authors": ["Mickey Djuric"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ca", "sentiment": -0.092}